{
  "stem": "24885.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He emptied out an apartment complex which used to be a Jewish section in Stuttgart West, and we were moved in there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were assigned apartments.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had-- our apartment was four or five people-- a two bedroom apartment, which was palatial.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had a kitchen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had our own food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had our own kitchen, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They took a, a restaurant from nearby.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they supplied the food and cooked and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we went in there to eat every day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And if you managed on your own something, you could cook in your own house if you had it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then my youngest brother-- this is when the United Nations Relief Agency seeked out the people 13 or 14 years younger and put them into a school which was called a Aglasterhausen.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In beginning of '46, early '46, they took them all to the United States, just those young people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We, in '46-- this man who was liberated with me, he had a leather factory.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he knew the family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "As a matter of fact during the war, I think I mentioned, he lived with my aunt and cousins and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He said, Harry, come with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he-- since this man Freudenberg came to his factory and took away the leather or so on, he went back to him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And he wanted some compensation, something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Well, the Freudenbergs were more civilized than a lot of other Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Even so, from what I understand, they took over several Jewish factories of leather in Germany and paid a pittance for it, but they later made up for it or so on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "He said, we'll help you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There's a man here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He's a German, but he worked for the Jewish leather factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
